        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 8 at 8:23AM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...A band of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility to
less than one mile.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 822 AM EDT, a band of heavy snow was along
a line extending from Black Moshannon State Park to Mcalisterville
and moving southeast at 30 MPH.

LOCATIONS IMPACTED INCLUDE...
Yeagertown, Alfarata, Houserville, Reedsville, Mifflintown,
Siglerville, Pleasant Gap, State College Regional Airport, Park
Forest Village, State College, Centre Hall, Unionville, Reeds Gap
State Park, Highland Park, Potters Mills, and Pennsylvania State
University.

This includes Interstate 99 from mile markers 65 to 80.

SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
